    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "But wait, you just said \"the law must apply equally to all citizens.\" Doesn't that basically mean that religious exemptions are inherently problematic or even wrong? If the goal is a functional democracy, shouldn't we prioritize the secular rule of law over these special religious privileges? It seems like you're saying the secular side is the only way to keep things stable.",
